able (dark), decrease quantity to <b>1 tbsp<b> and add <b>1 tbsp<b> sunflower oil.","These shao mai are usually served without a sauce; however you can mix <b>2 tbsp soy<b> sauce with <b>3-5 drops<b> vinegar and serve as a dip if you wish.","To save time, use ready-made yellow wonton wrappers, available in Asian supermarkets. You can cut the corners off to make them round, or just use them as they are.","Add <b>15 g spring<b> onions, roughly chopped, in <b>step 4.<b>","<strong>Vegetarian shao mai:<\/strong> Instead of <b>steps 4<b> <b>and 5,<b> place <b>400 g mixed<b> fresh mushrooms, <b>5 g fresh<b> ginger, thinly sliced, <b>50 g carrots<b> and <b>30 g oil<b> in mixing bowl, chop <b><strong>3 sec\/speed 5,<\/strong><b> and sauté <b><strong>5 min\/120°C\/speed .<\/strong><b> Add <b>120 g rice<b> (round or long grain), <b>½ tsp salt,<b> <b>1 tsp sugar,<b> <b>2 tsp soy<b> sauce and cook <b><strong>8 min\/100°C\/\/speed 0.5.<\/strong><b> Transfer the filling to a bowl and proceed as described in <b>step 6.<b> In <b>step 7,<b> steam <strong>25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1.<\/strong>","<strong>Fish shao mai:<\/strong> Instead of <b>steps 4<b> <b>and 5,<b> add <b>500 g skinless<b> white fish fillets (cut in pieces), <b>5 g fresh<b> ginger, thinly sliced, <b>8 sprigs<b> coriander (leaves only), <b>1 tsp sugar,<b> <b>2 tsp sesame<b> oil, <b>2 tsp soy<b> sauce, <b>1 tsp cornflour,<b> <b>1 tsp salt<b> and <b>¼ tsp ground<b> white pepper and mix <b><strong>7 sec\/ speed 5.<\/strong><b> Transfer the filling to a bowl and proceed as described in <b>step 6.<b> Before steaming in <b>step 7,<b> garnish each shao mai with a small coriander leaf."],"basicInfo":["advanced","1h 25m","2h","40 pieces"]}